HIV/AIDS: An samu ƙaruwar sababbin masu kamuwa da cutar da kashi 14 cikin 100 a China
China ta sanar da cewa yawan mutanen da ke da cutar HIV da AIDS a kasar ya karu da kashi 14 cikin dari.
Ma'aikatan kiwon lafiya sun ce wannan ya kai mutane fiye da 820,000.
A cikin kwata na biyu na 2018 kadai, adadin waɗanda aka ba da rahoton sun ƙaru da kusan 40 000.
Wannan canji ne da ya nuna cewa yawancin waɗanda suka kamu da cutar suna kamuwa da ita ta hanyar jima'i.
A dā, cutar tana yaɗuwa sosai a wasu sassan ƙasar Sin ta wurin jinin da aka yi wa mutane.
Amma, a wani taron da aka yi a lardin Yunnan, jami'an kiwon lafiya sun ce adadin irin waɗannan shari'o'in ya ragu zuwa kusan sifili.
Duk da haka, adadin mutanen da ke da cutar HIV da AIDS a China ya ƙaru da 100,000 a shekarar da ta gabata.
Cutar HIV ta hanyar jima'i babbar matsala ce ga al'ummar LGBT na kasar Sin.
Ba a sanya luwadi a matsayin laifi a kasar Sin ba tun 1997, amma nuna bambanci tsakanin jama'a ya kasance mai karfi tun daga lokacin.
An kiyasta cewa, a sakamakon tsarin dabi'u na gargajiya na ƙasar, kashi 70-90% na maza da suke yin jima'i da maza suna yin aure da mata.
A cikin waɗannan alaƙar, cutar tana yaduwa a lokatai da yawa saboda rashin isasshen kariya ta jima'i.
Tun 2003, gwamnatin kasar Sin ta samar da maganin cutar HIV ga kowa a matsayin wani bangare na shirin magance matsalar.
